{"type":"step-attempt","step":"spec-review","sessionId":"ae42fee4-26a5-40e2-a03a-e793aa51e8f7","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/bootstrap-commit-egress-ledger/spec-review-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/bootstrap-commit-egress-ledger/tasks.md","title":"T-04 TC-BE-001 test setup does not specify creating the requestFilePath file","rationale":"workspace-materializer.ts calls rejectSymlink(opts.requestFilePath) and fs.cp(opts.requestFilePath, ...) when requestFilePath is set. These are real fs operations that require the file to exist. T-04 specifies requestFilePath: '/tmp/request.md' but the task description has no instruction to create this file in beforeEach. Implementers must either create the file in a temp dir or add an fs mock, but the task is silent on which approach to use. Low impact — easily discovered during implementation."}],"evidence":{"checked":14,"skipped":0,"unverified":0},"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/bootstrap-commit-egress-ledger/design.md","title":"D2 'appendSynthesizedCommit already filters empty strings inside runInlineEgressCheck' is slightly imprecise","rationale":"verifyEgressLedger filters empty strings from the git rev-list output (via filter(Boolean)), not from the ledger itself. An empty string in the ledger would be inert because it would never appear in the git output OIDs list. The conclusion (empty string in ledger is meaningless and masks failure) is correct, but the stated mechanism is imprecise. No implementation impact — the direction (fail-closed, no sentinel) is sound."}]},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-22T12:16:02.484Z","endedAt":"2026-07-22T12:20:54.583Z","commitOid":"64c7796c4ad450a8b7ee4ff4cb231ad04b400757"}
